This paper deals with the problem of constructing a fault tolerant virtual backbone in wireless sensor networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and algorithms in computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a constant approximation algorithm for a specific problem in graph theory, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm in terms of connectivity and coverage, which is related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT).
